     </alternatives>
    </inline-formula> concentration in the aquifer will progressively decrease as the step input is not large enough to increase the overall aquifer concentration and at large times will achieve the equilibrium value, 
    <inline-formula id="IEq6" class="inline-formula">
     <alternatives class="alternatives">
      <tex-math id="M29" class="tex-math">\documentclass[12pt]{minimal} \usepackage{amsmath} \usepackage{wasysym} \usepackage{amsfonts} \usepackage{amssymb} \usepackage{amsbsy} \usepackage{mathrsfs} \usepackage{upgreek} \setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt} \begin{document}$$ \overline{W}/Q\left(1+K{t}_d\right) $$\end{document}</tex-math>
